1
00:00:08,083 --> 00:00:09,291
[drumroll]

2
00:00:13,291 --> 00:00:17,333
-[YOSHIAKI] Three, two, one!
-[AUDIENCE] Three, two, one!

3
00:00:22,958 --> 00:00:25,333
[cheering]

4
00:00:25,416 --> 00:00:27,875
[applause]

5
00:00:31,916 --> 00:00:33,875
[cheering continues
over monitor]

6
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:37,208
It's finally time.

7
00:00:37,291 --> 00:00:39,416
The thing
we've all been waiting for.

8
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:41,166
Tonight, Yoshiaki is
going to make

9
00:00:41,250 --> 00:00:43,833
an entire building disappear
right before our eyes.

10
00:00:43,916 --> 00:00:44,875
Are you ready?

11
00:00:44,958 --> 00:00:46,541
[audience cheering]

12
00:00:48,416 --> 00:00:51,458
[YOSHIAKI]
First, a target must be chosen.

13
00:00:51,541 --> 00:00:54,916
Even I don't know
what the target might be.

14
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,291
It could be Parliament,

15
00:00:56,375 --> 00:00:58,416
or the residence
of the Prime Minister.

16
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:01,583
You can never tell.
It could even be your own house.

17
00:01:01,666 --> 00:01:02,875
Is this cool?

18
00:01:02,958 --> 00:01:04,666
Did we get clearance to do this?

19
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:07,125
Who cares? We'll figure it out.

20
00:01:07,208 --> 00:01:08,833
This is pure gold.

21
00:01:08,916 --> 00:01:10,583
Go for it, man. Make it happen.

22
00:01:10,666 --> 00:01:11,916
[AUDIENCE cheering]

23
00:01:15,583 --> 00:01:16,625
[hatch opens]

24
00:01:22,791 --> 00:01:24,500
This one!

25
00:01:24,583 --> 00:01:26,000
[cheering continues
over monitor]

26
00:01:26,083 --> 00:01:27,833
[HOST] Looks like
the place has been chosen,

27
00:01:27,916 --> 00:01:29,125
ladies and gentlemen.

28
00:01:29,208 --> 00:01:31,041
Now, the question
on everyone's mind is.

29
00:01:31,125 --> 00:01:32,791
where could it be?

30
00:01:32,875 --> 00:01:35,916
My friends, this'll be
the last target of the night.

31
00:01:37,708 --> 00:01:40,250
The Lacuna Chemical Laboratory!

32
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:15,791
♪

33
00:03:41,041 --> 00:03:43,375
So we'd infiltrate
from our side?

34
00:03:43,458 --> 00:03:45,750
We'll hunt down the principal
they're protecting.

35
00:03:45,833 --> 00:03:47,625
Make him confess.

36
00:03:47,708 --> 00:03:50,375
It's a once in a lifetime chance
to bring down the Agency.

37
00:03:53,875 --> 00:03:56,541
You know, it might turn into
a battle against Tama-shi.

38
00:03:58,333 --> 00:04:00,083
Yeah, I know.

39
00:04:00,166 --> 00:04:01,833
But we don't have
much of a choice.

40
00:04:03,666 --> 00:04:05,166
-[YUKI] I...
-[gasps]

41
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:09,500
I agree.

42
00:04:10,666 --> 00:04:11,791
I wanna go, too.

43
00:04:13,250 --> 00:04:15,125
[TAKUYA]
Wait, are you sure?

44
00:04:15,208 --> 00:04:17,458
Shouldn't you stay here
with your little brother?

45
00:04:20,541 --> 00:04:22,916
Thanks for that, but, no.

46
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,541
Souma is stable now
and doesn't need me.

47
00:04:27,250 --> 00:04:28,333
[EIJI]
Understood.

48
00:04:28,416 --> 00:04:30,250
I'll notify you
if anything happens.

49
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:39,000
[YOSHIAKI]
I will now make the entire

50
00:04:39,083 --> 00:04:41,166
Lacuna Chemical
building disappear.

51
00:04:41,250 --> 00:04:42,541
If you live nearby,

52
00:04:42,625 --> 00:04:45,166
please feel free
to come watch live, in person.

53
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:48,083
Did he just say Lacuna Chemical?
That's really close by.

54
00:04:48,166 --> 00:04:50,250
Hey, Mom,
we should go check it out.

55
00:04:55,041 --> 00:04:57,500
[REPORTER 1] Think the Prime
Minister's lover's really here?

56
00:04:57,583 --> 00:04:58,875
[REPORTER 2]
You got that tip, too, huh?

57
00:04:58,958 --> 00:05:01,166
Yeah, but it sounds bogus.

58
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:02,708
[REPORTER 2] I'm right there
with you, buddy.

59
00:05:02,791 --> 00:05:06,083
[cell phones ringing]

60
00:05:06,166 --> 00:05:09,291
Hey, something's up.
Across town at Lacuna Chemical.

61
00:05:09,375 --> 00:05:10,541
[REPORTER 1]
Let's check it out.

62
00:05:10,625 --> 00:05:11,708
[REPORTER 2]
Sure.

63
00:05:11,791 --> 00:05:13,458
This tip seems
like a bust, anyway.

64
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:17,041
Okay, they're on the move.

65
00:05:17,125 --> 00:05:19,583
[overlapping chatter]

66
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:21,625
♪

67
00:05:26,541 --> 00:05:28,916
-What's going on?
-Go put in a report.

68
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,458
Wait, is Yoshiaki even here?

69
00:05:31,541 --> 00:05:33,291
[MAN]
He's already inside, isn't he?

70
00:05:33,375 --> 00:05:34,916
Dude, look at
all the TV stations.

71
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,250
Take a look behind me.

72
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:39,375
Tell us, do you plan
to let reporters inside?

73
00:05:39,458 --> 00:05:42,916
Come on, don't be stupid.
As if we could do that.

74
00:05:50,708 --> 00:05:52,625
[REPORTER] Excuse us.
Out of the way.

75
00:05:52,708 --> 00:05:54,500
[helicopter blades whirring]

76
00:05:57,708 --> 00:05:59,958
♪

77
00:06:02,666 --> 00:06:04,250
It has just begun.

78
00:06:06,875 --> 00:06:07,791
[scoffs]

79
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:15,041
[door opens]

80
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:20,666
Long day, am I right?

81
00:06:23,291 --> 00:06:26,375
Hey, you guys online,
are you seeing this?

82
00:06:26,458 --> 00:06:27,625
That's right, I'm in.

83
00:06:27,708 --> 00:06:29,166
This time,
I've infiltrated this place

84
00:06:29,250 --> 00:06:31,833
to help Yoshiaki
with his special show.

85
00:06:31,916 --> 00:06:34,625
I'm inside
the Lacuna Chemical Laboratory.

86
00:06:34,708 --> 00:06:36,875
There are actually some pretty
crazy rumors out there

87
00:06:36,958 --> 00:06:38,500
about this institution.

88
00:06:38,583 --> 00:06:39,750
I'm hoping
I might get a chance

89
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:41,708
to look into those
while I'm here, too.

90
00:06:44,916 --> 00:06:45,750
Hmm?

91
00:06:46,916 --> 00:06:48,500
[indistinct conversations]

92
00:06:49,541 --> 00:06:51,666
[YOSHIAKI]
Right now, there's a live stream

93
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:54,750
coming from inside
the Lacuna Chemical Laboratory.

94
00:06:54,833 --> 00:06:57,166
[audience murmuring]

95
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:59,625
That means you'll all be able
to see the truth,

96
00:06:59,708 --> 00:07:01,083
with your own eyes.

97
00:07:02,166 --> 00:07:05,458
Everyone here now,
and everyone watching live,

98
00:07:05,541 --> 00:07:07,041
look for yourselves.

99
00:07:07,125 --> 00:07:09,750
Confirm it with your own senses.

100
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:11,625
What the hell
is he talking about?

101
00:07:11,708 --> 00:07:15,166
Wait. Keep filming,
this is good content.

102
00:07:16,250 --> 00:07:20,041
But, like, he can't really make
the building disappear, right?

103
00:07:20,125 --> 00:07:21,875
[helicopter blades whirring]

104
00:07:23,625 --> 00:07:25,916
♪

105
00:07:28,166 --> 00:07:30,083
[YUKI screaming in pain]

106
00:07:30,166 --> 00:07:32,041
[rapid beeping]

107
00:07:33,666 --> 00:07:35,500
[gasps]

108
00:07:35,583 --> 00:07:36,958
[machine powering on]

109
00:07:43,250 --> 00:07:44,166
[GEEK]
Holy crap.

110
00:07:44,250 --> 00:07:45,208
Look at this over here, guys.

111
00:07:45,291 --> 00:07:46,875
I mean, there it is,

112
00:07:46,958 --> 00:07:49,916
this thing was obviously made
to hold down human beings.

113
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,208
Check it out.

114
00:07:51,291 --> 00:07:53,208
Headgear and restraints?

115
00:07:53,291 --> 00:07:55,458
This a pharmaceutical company,
right?

116
00:07:55,541 --> 00:07:57,666
Why the heck
would they ever need this stuff?

117
00:07:57,750 --> 00:07:59,541
[over cell phones]
This means the rumors are true,

118
00:07:59,625 --> 00:08:01,208
they're doing
human experimentation!

119
00:08:01,291 --> 00:08:03,958
What? That's nuts.
Is that really true?

120
00:08:04,041 --> 00:08:05,458
I guess so.

121
00:08:05,541 --> 00:08:09,041
-Wait. Did he just say Lacuna?
-Yeah, that's right.

122
00:08:09,125 --> 00:08:11,291
I've already gotten
an informal offer from there.

123
00:08:11,375 --> 00:08:14,250
Hey, Yoshiaki's saying
something now.

124
00:08:16,208 --> 00:08:19,375
I lost my parents
at a very young age.

125
00:08:19,458 --> 00:08:21,500
My brother and I, we were
sent to a children's home...

126
00:08:21,583 --> 00:08:23,125
I'm not responsible for this.

127
00:08:23,208 --> 00:08:25,500
You get it, though, right?
This feeling?

128
00:08:25,583 --> 00:08:27,583
Broadcasting should
always be like this.

129
00:08:27,666 --> 00:08:29,291
It's freakin' incredible.

130
00:08:29,375 --> 00:08:31,375
[YOSHIAKI on monitor]
Unfortunately,

131
00:08:31,458 --> 00:08:33,666
the children who lived there
were used as subjects

132
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:35,708
for human experimentation,

133
00:08:35,791 --> 00:08:38,541
and the company behind it was...

134
00:08:38,625 --> 00:08:39,916
Lacuna Chemical.

135
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,125
Well, it certainly
doesn't look staged.

136
00:08:43,208 --> 00:08:44,791
This is gonna be
one hell of a lawsuit.

137
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:49,625
[CROWD murmuring]

138
00:08:51,166 --> 00:08:53,500
Is there any truth
to the allegations?

139
00:08:53,583 --> 00:08:55,333
Was there human experimentation?

140
00:08:55,416 --> 00:08:56,583
Sir, you have to go.

141
00:08:56,666 --> 00:08:58,541
[overlapping chatter]

142
00:09:00,041 --> 00:09:01,958
[RESEARCHER 1]
Hurry up, throw this away.

143
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:03,708
[RESEARCHER 2]
You, too. Follow this list.

144
00:09:03,791 --> 00:09:05,208
[RESEARCHER 3]
Yeah, that goes.

145
00:09:05,291 --> 00:09:07,208
[RESEARCHER 2]
This, too.

146
00:09:07,291 --> 00:09:10,833
To think, they actually have
the gall to come and attack us.

147
00:09:10,916 --> 00:09:12,875
Stupid pests.

148
00:09:29,416 --> 00:09:32,000
What are you doing, anyway?
Hurry up, would you?

149
00:09:32,083 --> 00:09:33,625
[RESEARCHER]
Right. I'm sorry, sir.

150
00:09:33,708 --> 00:09:35,000
-[door opens]
-[gasps]

151
00:09:35,083 --> 00:09:38,000
You're looking well, Principal.

152
00:09:38,083 --> 00:09:41,416
So, it's you.
What are you doing here?

153
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:42,500
[GEEK]
Oh, that's simple.

154
00:09:42,583 --> 00:09:43,833
We just happened to hear

155
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:45,208
that you were
the overseeing director

156
00:09:45,291 --> 00:09:46,916
of this place now, right?

157
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:50,375
From principal of Light of Hope
to a managing director.

158
00:09:50,458 --> 00:09:53,291
That's quite the promotion
for a guy like you.

159
00:09:53,375 --> 00:09:54,708
Care to take this time

160
00:09:54,791 --> 00:09:56,958
to explain yourself
to the world, sir?

161
00:09:57,041 --> 00:09:58,333
We're listening.

162
00:09:58,416 --> 00:09:59,958
No, I have nothing
to say to you.

163
00:10:01,291 --> 00:10:03,416
The least you can do is
speak the truth.

164
00:10:04,791 --> 00:10:07,625
Tell us, how long
were you involved?

165
00:10:07,708 --> 00:10:09,541
You don't understand.
I've done nothing.

166
00:10:09,625 --> 00:10:11,333
I'm a victim, like the rest.

167
00:10:11,416 --> 00:10:14,583
I don't even get how you live
with yourself, old man.

168
00:10:14,666 --> 00:10:17,625
Think about all the children
who were sacrificed.

169
00:10:17,708 --> 00:10:19,833
[GEEK/YUKI gasp]

170
00:10:19,916 --> 00:10:21,125
[TAKUYA groans]
Shit!

171
00:10:22,625 --> 00:10:23,708
[STUDENT]
Oh, it dropped.

172
00:10:23,791 --> 00:10:25,666
Who were the guys in black?

173
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,583
-Scary.
-Whoa.

174
00:10:27,666 --> 00:10:29,083
Yoshiaki's followers
have increased

175
00:10:29,166 --> 00:10:31,166
by, like, 200,000.

176
00:10:34,791 --> 00:10:36,750
♪

177
00:10:40,666 --> 00:10:42,666
[YOSHIAKI]
Hey, what's going on?

178
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:44,791
How are things
progressing for them?

179
00:10:44,875 --> 00:10:47,708
It's going great.
You did really well.

180
00:10:47,791 --> 00:10:48,666
Hmm.

181
00:10:49,666 --> 00:10:51,708
Put your trust
in the public now.

182
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:54,500
[YUJI]
As the records here prove,

183
00:10:54,583 --> 00:10:56,000
Lacuna had been sending

184
00:10:56,083 --> 00:10:58,125
large sums of money
to the academy.

185
00:10:59,125 --> 00:11:02,416
That principal was
definitely hired by Lacuna.

186
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:05,000
So it seems abundantly clear
that they're both involved

187
00:11:05,083 --> 00:11:07,041
with the human trafficking
we've uncovered.

188
00:11:08,375 --> 00:11:12,125
I have a sworn statement from
that magician with me, as well.

189
00:11:12,208 --> 00:11:15,666
This is our chance to bring
Negishi a little peace.

190
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:17,750
If we don't move now,
then when will we?

191
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:20,916
[YOSHIAKI]
Right now, there's a live stream

192
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,833
coming from inside
the Lacuna Chemical Laboratory.

193
00:11:23,916 --> 00:11:26,291
That means you'll all be able
to see the truth,

194
00:11:26,375 --> 00:11:27,833
with your own eyes.

195
00:11:27,916 --> 00:11:29,250
Everyone here, now...

196
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:31,458
[MEN groaning]

197
00:11:38,208 --> 00:11:41,666
[TAKUYA] Well, that sucked.
What a pain.

198
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:44,166
This is the end for you guys.

199
00:11:44,250 --> 00:11:45,750
[PRINCIPAL]
It couldn't be helped, though.

200
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:48,583
We had to have money
to keep the academy open.

201
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:50,291
What was I supposed to do?

202
00:11:50,375 --> 00:11:53,833
I couldn't just let the children
end up homeless on the streets.

203
00:11:54,833 --> 00:11:57,833
It wasn't my fault.
I had no choice.

204
00:11:57,916 --> 00:11:59,666
[gasps]
Please.

205
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:02,250
I really was thinking
only of the children.

206
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:05,000
You have to believe me,
I'm begging you.

207
00:12:06,291 --> 00:12:08,166
[NEWSCASTER] The president
and vice president

208
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:09,541
of Lacuna Chemical

209
00:12:09,625 --> 00:12:12,125
have both been requested
to volunteer themselves

210
00:12:12,208 --> 00:12:13,041
for questioning.

211
00:12:14,041 --> 00:12:16,083
First Investigating Division.

212
00:12:16,166 --> 00:12:17,416
Kakizaki.

213
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:19,375
Sorry, but we'd like
the responsible parties

214
00:12:19,458 --> 00:12:21,166
to come with us.

215
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:23,583
My, you seem awfully
well prepared for this.

216
00:12:23,666 --> 00:12:25,833
So did you bring a warrant?

217
00:12:25,916 --> 00:12:27,333
It's voluntary.

218
00:12:27,416 --> 00:12:30,458
You're free to refuse.
It's your choice.

219
00:12:30,541 --> 00:12:32,166
-[TAIYO] Well, let's go.
-[TSUKI gasps]

220
00:12:36,041 --> 00:12:37,916
A wise decision.

221
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:38,916
[scoffs]

222
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:50,541
I'm happy to say you won't get
to look that smug for long.

223
00:12:50,625 --> 00:12:52,166
We'll have warrants soon.

224
00:12:53,375 --> 00:12:55,208
[OFFICER] Yeah, there's
a mountain of charges.

225
00:13:00,375 --> 00:13:01,916
It's almost time.

226
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,375
[overlapping chatter]

227
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:15,625
Yuki, you have to go back.

228
00:13:15,708 --> 00:13:17,208
-[YUKI] Huh?
-What's wrong?

229
00:13:17,291 --> 00:13:19,166
Souma's condition
has changed again.

230
00:13:19,250 --> 00:13:20,208
[gasps]

231
00:13:26,708 --> 00:13:28,375
-[door opens]
-Hmm?

232
00:13:28,458 --> 00:13:30,791
[YUJI gasps]
Commissioner.

233
00:13:32,916 --> 00:13:35,000
Thanks for your work,
you're free to go.

234
00:13:35,083 --> 00:13:36,958
Uh... But, sir--

235
00:13:37,041 --> 00:13:38,958
[COMMISSIONER]
Did you not hear what I said?

236
00:13:40,083 --> 00:13:41,041
[grunts]

237
00:13:42,333 --> 00:13:43,250
[door closes]

238
00:13:48,250 --> 00:13:49,750
[COMMISSIONER]
My sincerest apologies.

239
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:51,666
Please, leave the rest to me.

240
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,541
[rumbling]

241
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:01,666
[TAKUYA]
What's going on?

242
00:14:06,541 --> 00:14:08,500
[static]

243
00:14:08,583 --> 00:14:09,541
[gasps]

244
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:12,500
[TAKUYA]
What happened?

245
00:14:12,583 --> 00:14:14,291
[KIKYO]
I don't understand.

246
00:14:14,375 --> 00:14:16,416
There's a distortion
in gravitational waves

247
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:17,875
emitting from Souma.

248
00:14:17,958 --> 00:14:19,166
Huh?

249
00:14:19,250 --> 00:14:20,875
But that's crazy.

250
00:14:20,958 --> 00:14:23,166
Takuya, listen.

251
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:24,666
This is the same as the Lost.

252
00:14:24,750 --> 00:14:25,791
[grunts]

253
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:29,833
The Lost is happening again?

254
00:14:29,916 --> 00:14:31,375
[ALL gasp]

255
00:14:31,458 --> 00:14:33,416
♪

256
00:14:37,416 --> 00:14:38,458
[KIKYO gasps]

257
00:14:42,666 --> 00:14:44,125
[groaning]

258
00:14:46,166 --> 00:14:47,083
[EIJI]
It's bad.

259
00:14:47,166 --> 00:14:48,708
We have to get out of here.

260
00:14:48,791 --> 00:14:50,666
But you have to save Souma!

261
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:51,958
[SOUMA groans sharply]

262
00:14:52,041 --> 00:14:53,291
[EIJI]
I'm sorry.

263
00:14:56,541 --> 00:14:58,708
I'm afraid we've already
passed that point.

264
00:15:00,458 --> 00:15:01,916
[gasping]

265
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:04,750
[EIJI] Kikyo, send out
an anonymous evacuation warning

266
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:06,041
for the area.

267
00:15:08,416 --> 00:15:11,375
You know, I don't remember
hearing that this was the plan.

268
00:15:11,458 --> 00:15:15,541
It was simply the best way to
make use of the useless Souma.

269
00:15:15,625 --> 00:15:17,333
[TSUKI]
I can't argue with that.

270
00:15:17,416 --> 00:15:19,375
He was very unstable.

271
00:15:19,458 --> 00:15:21,416
The boy can't even seem
to control himself

272
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:23,750
without an artifact,
which is pathetic.

273
00:15:23,833 --> 00:15:25,083
A failed creation.

274
00:15:25,166 --> 00:15:28,375
Although, when Tsuki's Tears
was destroyed,

275
00:15:28,458 --> 00:15:31,458
Souma was able
to hold it together.

276
00:15:31,541 --> 00:15:33,958
[TAIYO] That's because
she was close to him.

277
00:15:34,041 --> 00:15:35,958
-[SUZUNA] It can't be.
-[TSUKI gasps]

278
00:15:36,041 --> 00:15:38,500
His big sister
acted as an artifact.

279
00:15:38,583 --> 00:15:40,083
It's true.

280
00:15:40,166 --> 00:15:41,291
This time, he was triggered

281
00:15:41,375 --> 00:15:43,375
because his sister
wasn't around.

282
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:49,541
That energy cannot
be compared to the Lost

283
00:15:49,625 --> 00:15:51,791
that occurred
three years ago.

284
00:15:51,875 --> 00:15:54,333
♪

285
00:16:10,416 --> 00:16:12,125
-[WOMAN gasps]
-[overlapping chatter]

286
00:16:21,666 --> 00:16:24,708
They actually meant to drag us
out into the open, didn't they?

287
00:16:25,833 --> 00:16:27,000
Pitiable.

288
00:16:27,083 --> 00:16:29,416
Fun bit of entertainment.

289
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:33,708
No matter what happens now,
the Lost is going to occur.

290
00:16:41,208 --> 00:16:43,125
-[horn blaring]
-[TAKUYA] You all right?

291
00:16:43,208 --> 00:16:44,333
[KIKYO] Yes.

292
00:16:44,416 --> 00:16:46,375
[EIJI]
Takuya, this place is dangerous.

293
00:16:46,458 --> 00:16:48,416
We have no choice
but to evacuate.

294
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:51,291
[grunts]

295
00:16:51,375 --> 00:16:53,416
[panting]

296
00:16:55,791 --> 00:16:57,916
[TAKUYA]
Okay, how can we stop Souma?

297
00:17:01,833 --> 00:17:04,916
Listen, that kid is
a ticking bomb right now.

298
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:07,208
The only saving grace
at this point

299
00:17:07,291 --> 00:17:09,166
is that he's a living organism.

300
00:17:10,458 --> 00:17:13,250
And by that, you mean...

301
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:16,125
I mean if Souma's vital activity
were to shut down,

302
00:17:16,208 --> 00:17:18,166
well, then...

303
00:17:18,250 --> 00:17:19,125
[YUMIKO]
No way.

304
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:22,333
[YUKI]
That's it. I'm going.

305
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:23,458
[ALL gasp]

306
00:17:25,666 --> 00:17:27,583
[TAKUYA]
You can't do this.

307
00:17:27,666 --> 00:17:29,958
[YUKI]
I have to try to take him on.

308
00:17:30,041 --> 00:17:31,708
[TAKUYA]
That's crazy, it's impossible.

309
00:17:31,791 --> 00:17:33,125
[YUKI]
You don't know that!

310
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:37,708
Weren't you the one
who told me...

311
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:40,333
I won't know till I try?

312
00:17:40,416 --> 00:17:41,750
[groans softly]

313
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:42,916
Hmm...

314
00:17:45,291 --> 00:17:46,958
Hang on tight!

315
00:17:47,041 --> 00:17:49,041
♪

316
00:18:04,791 --> 00:18:06,333
[BOTH scream]

317
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:13,583
[groans]

318
00:18:13,666 --> 00:18:14,500
Yuki.

319
00:18:14,583 --> 00:18:16,833
♪

320
00:18:25,083 --> 00:18:25,958
Akira.

321
00:18:32,458 --> 00:18:33,708
[TAKUYA, weakly]
Where is she?

322
00:18:33,791 --> 00:18:35,333
[KOUTA]
You really don't have the time

323
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:37,333
to worry about anyone else.

324
00:18:37,416 --> 00:18:39,583
Not now.

325
00:18:39,666 --> 00:18:40,750
[gasps]

326
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:41,750
Kouta.

327
00:18:44,583 --> 00:18:45,541
[SOUMA MONSTER]
Don't come.

328
00:18:46,708 --> 00:18:47,791
I hate you.

329
00:18:48,833 --> 00:18:50,500
All of you.

330
00:18:50,583 --> 00:18:52,916
♪

331
00:18:57,416 --> 00:18:59,000
Go away!

332
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:02,083
[YUKI groans, screams]

333
00:19:12,625 --> 00:19:14,041
Souma.

334
00:19:14,125 --> 00:19:14,958
[SOUMA]
Don't...

335
00:19:16,250 --> 00:19:18,166
Don't look.

336
00:19:18,250 --> 00:19:20,083
Don't come.

337
00:19:20,166 --> 00:19:22,375
Go away.

338
00:19:22,458 --> 00:19:23,958
I hate you.

339
00:19:24,041 --> 00:19:26,666
I hate you.
I hate you.

340
00:19:26,750 --> 00:19:28,750
I hate you.

341
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:30,625
[groaning]

342
00:19:30,708 --> 00:19:32,250
Little brother.

343
00:19:32,333 --> 00:19:34,291
♪

344
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:41,458
I'm sorry.

345
00:19:42,625 --> 00:19:43,666
[SOUMA MONSTER groans]

346
00:19:46,958 --> 00:19:47,916
[gasps]

347
00:19:49,333 --> 00:19:51,291
♪

348
00:19:57,166 --> 00:19:58,541
[sobbing]

349
00:19:58,625 --> 00:20:00,708
♪

350
00:20:17,791 --> 00:20:20,125
[SOUMA MONSTER]
Stop this.

351
00:20:20,208 --> 00:20:21,791
Don't look.

352
00:20:21,875 --> 00:20:23,875
Go away.

353
00:20:23,958 --> 00:20:25,500
[thumping]

354
00:20:25,583 --> 00:20:28,791
[SOUMA] I'm scared.
I don't want this.

355
00:20:28,875 --> 00:20:32,750
-[YUKI gasps]
-[SOUMA] Sis, I don't wanna die.

356
00:20:38,916 --> 00:20:40,416
[gasps]

357
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:41,375
Souma!

358
00:20:43,083 --> 00:20:44,958
Please help me.

359
00:20:45,041 --> 00:20:47,041
Please, Yuki, will you?

360
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,458
Stop, sis. You have to.

361
00:21:09,750 --> 00:21:12,125
[SOUMA MONSTER]
Sis, stop.

362
00:21:25,041 --> 00:21:28,375
[TAIYO] You're saying
it didn't occur. Why?

363
00:21:28,458 --> 00:21:30,333
[SUZUNA]
Even with my power,

364
00:21:30,416 --> 00:21:32,666
I wasn't able to see
this possibility.

365
00:21:33,666 --> 00:21:34,791
[grunts in frustration]

366
00:21:37,375 --> 00:21:38,625
Daichi.

367
00:21:41,166 --> 00:21:43,916
Just how much do you plan
to get in my way?

368
00:23:36,958 --> 00:23:37,875
♪

369
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:38,791
[inaudible]

370
00:23:43,666 --> 00:23:46,000
[YUKI]
Next Episode, "Fate."

